a.src=document.location.protocol+&quot;//script.crazyegg.com/pages/scripts/0023/1544.js?&quot;+Math.floor(new Date().getTime()/3600000);
a.async=true;a.type=&quot;text/javascript&quot;;b.parentNode.insertBefore(a,b)}, 1);
//]]&gt;
</script><br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>At North County High, more than two-thirds of students generally do not pass the exams, meaning no college credit. Principal Cares says they’re working to improve that rate. Even without the college credit, she says students develop skills like writing and critical thinking that will serve them in college.<br /><br /></p>"},{"content":"<p>“They’re still learning those skills that are pushing them forward,” Cares says.<br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p>Junior Nevay Archuleta didn’t pass her first AP test last year in Government. But, she says taking the class still changed how she thinks about herself and her future. She’s taking two more AP classes this year.<br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p>“Before AP, I thought I was definitely like too average for college,” she says. “But I think now that they see that I’ve challenged myself, they’re going to be more impressed.”<br /><br /></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<hr />"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p><a href="http://professionals.collegeboard.com/testing/ap/coordinate/fee-assistance"></a></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<div class="large blue awesome">$91</div>"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"content":"<p><a href="https://professionals.collegeboard.com/testing/waivers/guidelines/ap"></a></p>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<div class="large blue awesome">$53</div>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><a href="https://professionals.collegeboard.com/testing/ap/coordinate/details-state"></a></p>"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<div class="large blue awesome">13</div>"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<p><a href="http://www.guidestar.org/organizations/13-1623965/college-entrance-examination-board.aspx"></a></p>"},{"content":"<div class="large blue awesome">$795,817,602</div>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p><a href="http://www.ed.gov/news/press-releases/education-department-awards-40-states-dc-and-virgin-islands-284-million-grants-help-low-income-students-take-advanced-placement-tests"></a></p>","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<div class="large blue awesome">$28,483,000</div>","type":"text/html"},{"type":"text/html","content":"<br />"},{"content":"<br />","type":"text/html"},{"content":"<p><em>*The College Board provides a $29 fee reduction per exam for students with financial need. For each AP exam taken with a fee reduction, the school forgoes its $9 rebate, resulting in a cost of $53 per exam for the student. <a href="https://professionals.collegeboard.com/testing/ap/coordinate/details-state">Many states use federal and state funding to further reduce the exam fee</a> for these students.</em><br /><br /></p>","type":"text/html"}]
